<heading>health - Validate node structure.</heading>

<rule/>

<heading level="2">
Usage
</heading>
<pre>
  health
</pre>

<heading level="2">
Description
</heading>

<paragraph>
Scans the node tree and validates the structural integrity of each node.
Each node is checked for a readable <code>yak.yml</code>,
a registered executor, and an existing <code>app.py</code> entry point.
No Python modules are loaded — validation is purely structural.
</paragraph>

<heading level="2">
Icons
</heading>

<pre>
  ✓   valid
  ⚠   degraded
  ✗   invalid
</pre>

<heading level="2">
See also
</heading>

<paragraph>
<code>info</code> — show detailed node information.
</paragraph>
